---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/docs-layout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../components/code-block.astro';
import ComponentPreview from '../../components/component-preview.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Introduction - DocyUI" description="Beautiful, accessible, and customizable components for React and Vue">
  <div class="pb-12 pt-8">
    <div class="flex flex-col items-start gap-4 md:flex-row md:justify-between md:gap-8">
      <div class="flex-1 space-y-4">
        <h1 class="inline-block font-heading text-4xl tracking-tight lg:text-5xl">
          <span class="docyui-gradient-text">Introduction</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
          DocyUI is a collection of beautifully-designed, accessible components that you can copy and paste into your apps. Built for React and Vue.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground">
          Multi-framework support. Open source. Copy and paste.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- What is DocyUI -->
  <div class="pb-12">
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading tracking-tight">What is DocyUI?</h2>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground">
        This is <strong>not a component library</strong>. It's a collection of reusable components that you can copy and paste into your apps.
      </p>
      
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          DocyUI is based on the excellent work of <a href="https://ui.shadcn.com" class="text-foreground underline hover:no-underline">shadcn/ui</a> and extends it with:
        </p>
        
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-muted-foreground">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">•</span>
            <span><strong>Multi-framework support</strong> - Components for both React and Vue</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">•</span>
            <span><strong>Enhanced CLI tooling</strong> - Streamlined component installation and management</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">•</span>
            <span><strong>11 color palettes</strong> - Carefully crafted themes for every project</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">•</span>
            <span><strong>TypeScript first</strong> - Full type safety and IntelliSense support</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="bg-muted/50 rounded-lg p-4 border">
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          <strong>Think of it as a starter kit.</strong> Use the components as a starting point and customize them to match your needs. 
          You have full control over the code and can modify it however you want.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Key Principles -->
  <div class="pb-12">
    <div class="space-y-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading tracking-tight">Key Principles</h2>
      
      <!-- Copy and Paste -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-semibold">Copy and Paste</h3>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          Components are designed to be copied and pasted directly into your project. No npm installs, no peer dependencies, no breaking changes.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground ml-4">
          <li>• You own the code and can modify it as needed</li>
          <li>• No external dependencies to manage</li>
          <li>• Full control over styling and behavior</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Multi-Framework -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-semibold">Multi-Framework</h3>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          Built for both React and Vue with consistent APIs and styling. Use the same components across different projects.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground ml-4">
          <li>• React components with TypeScript support</li>
          <li>• Vue 3 components with Composition API</li>
          <li>• Consistent design language across frameworks</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Accessible -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-semibold">Accessible</h3>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          Built on top of Radix UI (React) and Radix Vue with full keyboard navigation, screen reader support, and ARIA attributes.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground ml-4">
          <li>• Full keyboard navigation support</li>
          <li>• Screen reader compatible</li>
          <li>• WCAG 2.1 compliant</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Customizable -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-semibold">Customizable</h3>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          Built with Tailwind CSS and CSS variables. Easy to customize with your own design tokens and color schemes.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground ml-4">
          <li>• CSS variables for easy theming</li>
          <li>• 11 built-in color palettes</li>
          <li>• Dark mode support out of the box</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Example Component -->
  <div class="pb-12">
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading tracking-tight">Example</h2>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground">
        Here's an example of a Button component with multiple variants:
      </p>
      
      <ComponentPreview name="button" />
      
      <div class="bg-muted/50 rounded-lg p-4 border">
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          <strong>Installation:</strong> <code class="bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">npx docyui@latest add button</code>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Quick Start -->
  <div class="pb-12">
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading tracking-tight">Quick Start</h2>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground">
        Get started with DocyUI in seconds. Choose your framework and run the init command.
      </p>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 border rounded-lg space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-[#61DAFB]" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
